    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1819-08-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1819-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="104"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">McCulloch</persName>, collector, to
                        Mr. <persName type="to">Dowry</persName>, surveyor.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Custom-House, Baltimore</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Collector’s Office</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1819-08-25">
                        <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 25, 1819</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: It is alleged that Captain Daniels has not only
                    repaired: the brig: Negreda, a Spanish prize, in which he arrived, but has
                    altered her masts, decks, and rigging, as well as her armament, that *her
                    platform is renewed and fixed, that her mainmast, formerly schooner-rigged, <pb
                        facs="0512" n="498" xml:id="pg_498"/> is now square rigged, her guns
                    formerly on slides are now on carriages, sixteen in number, and that some brass
                    pieces are added to her after-deck or bulwarks, which she had not before. <seg
                        type="margin">[129]</seg>
                </p>
                <p>Please to order two officers, one of them the officer who inspected her at
                    arrival, to visit and strictly examine her and report to me on these and other
                    particulars in her case.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>J. H. McCULLOCH.</item>
                            <item>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lowry</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Surveyor Port of Baltimore.</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
